================================================================================
Aesthetic + structural credits
================================================================================

Mythological references throughout follow the standard reconstructions
of Hesiod (Theogony, Works and Days), Homer (Iliad, Odyssey), and the
Library of Apollodorus. Specific role assignments (e.g., Mnemosyne as
audit-of-record discipline, Argos as decentralized swarm) are this
project's architectural choices, not historical claims about Greek
religion.

================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

This project contains no third-party libraries beyond the Python
standard library at the substrate level. Deployments built on top of
Olympus add their own dependencies via their own NOTICE files.
